ns4:Method.description: Return a list of coding schemes and versions that are supported by this service, along with their status.
ns4:Method.name: getSupportedCodingSchemes

ns4:Method.description: Returns the set of all (or all active) concepts in the specified coding scheme.
ns4:Method.name: getCodingSchemeConcepts

ns4:Method.description: Return the last time that the content of this service was changed; null if no changes have occurred. Tag assignments do not count as service changes for this purpose.
ns4:Method.name: getLastUpdateTime

ns4:Method.description: Return detailed coding scheme information given a specific tag or version identifier.
ns4:Method.name: resolveCodingScheme

ns4:Method.description: Returns the full description of all supported match algorithms.
ns4:Method.name: getMatchAlgorithms

ns4:Method.description: Returns the node graph as represented in the particular relationship set in the coding scheme.
ns4:Method.name: getNodeGraph

ns4:Method.description: Returns a description of all registered extensions used to provide additional sorting of query results in the given context. Note: The returned list will include any 'built-in' sort algorithms in addition to extensions externally packaged and registered to the service.
ns4:Method.name: getSortAlgorithms

ns4:Method.description: Returns a description of all registered extensions used to implement application-specific behavior that is centrally accessible from a LexBIGService. Note that only generic extensions (base class GenericExtension) will be listed here. All other classes are retrievable at the appropriate interface point (filter, sort, etc).
ns4:Method.name: getGenericExtensions

ns4:Method.description: Returns an instance of the application-specific extension registered with the given name.
ns4:Method.name: getGenericExtension

ns4:Method.description: Returns a description of all registered extensions used to provide additional filtering of query results.
ns4:Method.name: getFilterExtensions

ns4:Method.description: Resolve a reference to the history api servicing the given coding scheme.
ns4:Method.name: getHistoryService

ns4:Method.description: Return an interface to perform system-wide query over metadata for loaded code systems and providers.
ns4:Method.name: getServiceMetadata

ns4:Method.description: Returns an instance of the sort extension registered with the given name.
ns4:Method.name: getSortAlgorithm

ns4:Method.description: Returns an instance of the filter extension registered with the given name.
ns4:Method.name: getFilter

ns4:Method.description: Return coding scheme copyright given a specific tag or version identifier.
ns4:Method.name: resolveCodingSchemeCopyright

ns4:Method.description: Sets the Security Token for the given Coding Scheme.
ns4:Method.name: setSecurityToken

ns132:Method.description: Resolve all of the coded nodes in the list, sorting by the supplied property (if any), resolving the supplied properties, resolving coded entries to the supplied depth and resolving associations to the supplied * depth.
ns132:Method.name: resolveAsList

ns132:Method.description: Return a list of all of the associations in the graph that have the supplied source and target concepts or, if directOnly is false, all associations whose transitive closure has the supplied associations.
ns132:Method.name: listCodeRelationships

ns132:Method.description: Restrict the graph to concept codes (source and target) that originate from the supplied code system. Note: edges defined by other code systems will still be resolved if associated with both source and target nodes for the restricted code system.
ns132:Method.name: restrictToSourceCodeSystem

ns132:Method.description: Restrict the graph to edges that have concepts derived from the supplied code system as a target.
ns132:Method.name: restrictToTargetCodeSystem

ns132:Method.description: Restrict the graph to concept codes (source and target) that originate from the supplied code system. Note: edges defined by other code systems will still be resolved if associated with both source and target nodes for the restricted code system.
ns132:Method.name: restrictToCodeSystem

ns132:Method.description: Restrict the graph to associations that have one of the codes in the supplied list as target codes.
ns132:Method.name: restrictToTargetCodes

ns132:Method.description: Restrict the graph to associations that have one of the codes in the supplied list as source codes.
ns132:Method.name: restrictToSourceCodes

ns132:Method.description: Restrict the graph to the nodes that participate as a source or target of an association whose directional name matches the one provided and, if supplied, * the named association qualifiers. * A directional name is considered to be either the forward or reverse label * registered to an association defined by the ontology. Forward and reverse names * are optionally assigned to each association. For example, an association 'lineage' may have a forward name 'ancestorOf' and reverse name 'descendentOf'.
ns132:Method.name: restrictToDirectionalNames

ns132:Method.description: Restrict the graph to the nodes that participate as a source or target of the named association and, if supplied, the named association qualifiers.
ns132:Method.name: restrictToAssociations

ns132:Method.description: Return a graph that contains only the codes that are present in the supplied list, and all edges that still have a source and target code remaining.
ns132:Method.name: restrictToCodes

ns132:Method.description: Return the set of concepts and associations that are present in both graphs.
ns132:Method.name: intersect

ns132:Method.description: Return the union of the two graphs. Union, in this context, means that the resulting graph contains the unique set of coded entries (String independent) that are present in one or both of the graphs, and the unique combination of edges (associations) present in one or both of the graphs.
ns132:Method.name: union

ns132:Method.description: Determine whether the supplied concept code is in the graph.
ns132:Method.name: isCodeInGraph

ns132:Method.description: Transform the graph into a simple of list of concept codes, removing all association information.
ns132:Method.name: toNodeList

ns132:Method.description: Determine whether there is an directed edge (or transitive closure of an edge) from the source code to the target code in this graph. The last parameter determines whether only direct associations are considered or whether the transitive closure of the edge is used.
ns132:Method.name: areCodesRelated

ns132:Method.description: Return a list of all of the associations in the graph that have the supplied source and target concepts based on distance between them. Distance (or the No. of edges) for a direct association between a source and target codes is 1. Values if distance should be equal or greater than 1, otherwise exception is thrown. Resulting list is not based on associations source & target have, but on distance only.
ns132:Method.name: listCodeRelationships2

ns218:Method.description: Return detailed rendering information (including coding scheme summary, version and status information, reference links, etc) for the given coding scheme; null if not available.
ns218:Method.name: getRenderingDetail

ns218:Method.description: Return the coding schemes who supported association matching with associationName. The search is performed only for loaded coding schemes. *
ns218:Method.name: getCodingSchemesWithSupportedAssociation

ns218:Method.description: Returns the identifiers for hierarchical relationships available for navigation within a coding scheme. These identifiers can be submitted to the getHierarchyBroader() or getHierarchyNarrower() methods to navigate corresponding tree structures. Possible return values are defined by the LexBIG model (see http://informatics.mayo.edu/LexGrid/downloads/LexGrid%20Model/schemas/2009/01/EAwebpublish/index.htm).
ns218:Method.name: getHierarchyIDs

ns218:Method.description: Indicates if the given code is considered retired or inactive within context of the provided scheme.
ns218:Method.name: isCodeRetired

ns218:Method.description: Return the forward name for the identified association.
ns218:Method.name: getAssociationForwardName

ns218:Method.description: Return all the association forward name for the coding scheme.
ns218:Method.name: getAssociationForwardNames

ns218:Method.description: Return the reverse name for the identified association.
ns218:Method.name: getAssociationReverseName

ns218:Method.description: Return all the association reverse name for the coding scheme.
ns218:Method.name: getAssociationReverseNames

ns218:Method.description: Return true if directionalName is the forward name of an association for the coding scheme.
ns218:Method.name: isForwardName

ns218:Method.description: Return true if directionalName is the reverse name of an association for the coding scheme.
ns218:Method.name: isReverseName

ns218:Method.description: Return a representation of associations between a concept and its immediate decendents. The resolved association list represents the next branch of the hierarchy when visualized in a top (root) to bottom (leaf) representation.
ns218:Method.name: getHierarchyLevelNext

ns218:Method.description: Return a representation of associations between a concept and its immediate ancestor(s). The resolved association list represents the previous level of the hierarchy when visualized in a top (root) to bottom (leaf) representation.
ns218:Method.name: getHierarchyLevelPrev

ns218:Method.description: Return a representation of associations between a concept and hierarchical root node(s). The resolved association list represents the path within the hierarchy from traversed from bottom (leaf) to top (root).
ns218:Method.name: getHierarchyPathToRoot

ns218:Method.description: Returns all root nodes for the given hierarchy and coding scheme. Each root concept represents the conceptual start or narrowest point of a tree when visualizing the hierarchy.
ns218:Method.name: getHierarchyRoots

ns218:Method.description: Returns all root nodes for the given hierarchy as a CodeNodeSet, which can be further restricted. Each root concept represents the conceptual start or narrowest point of a tree when visualizing the hierarchy.
ns218:Method.name: getHierarchyRootSet

ns218:Method.description: Create a CodedNodeSet from a set of concept codes in a coding scheme.
ns218:Method.name: createCodeNodeSet

ns218:Method.description: Return all the association forward name and reverse name for the coding scheme.
ns218:Method.name: getAssociationForwardAndReverseNames

ns218:Method.description: Return the copyright text for the coding scheme.
ns218:Method.name: getCodingSchemeCopyright

ns348:Method.description: Return the next available concept reference, in order, from the underlying list. Note: This is effectively the same as performing next(1), but eliminates the need to continually unwrap the concept reference from the resolved list.
ns348:Method.name: next

ns348:Method.description: Return concept references from the underlying list, in order and up to the specified maximum.
ns348:Method.name: nextInt

ns348:Method.description: Return concept references from the underlying list, from the start point (inclusive) to the end point (exclusive). Calling this method has no effect on the next() calls - next() will still iterate * through the results in the same sequential order regardless of if this method has * been used. * * the result of numberRemaining() is not affected by calls to this method. * * Note: This method may return fewer results than requested even if there are still more results after the last result returned by the service. Note: The method is optional, and may not be implemented by all implementations. Note: Using this method in combination with Filters may cause significant performance reductions.
ns348:Method.name: get

ns348:Method.description: Return the next batch of resolved concept references.
ns348:Method.name: scroll

ns348:Method.description: True means that there still values that can be returned. False means all values have already been returned.
ns348:Method.name: hasNext

ns348:Method.description: Returns a count of the number of items remaining in the iterator. This is optional, and may only be an estimate. Implementations should return -1 if they cannot count or estimate the number remaining. Note: This method is not affected by calls to get(int, int). It only returns counts with respect to calls to next() or next(int).
ns348:Method.name: numberRemaining

ns385:Method.description: Return the list of change events identifying the immediate ancestors of the given concept reference.
ns385:Method.name: getAncestors

ns385:Method.description: Return a list of baselines supported by this service that were released on or after the first supplied date and were released on or before the second date. Returned baselines are arranged in sequential order, from earliest to latest.
ns385:Method.name: getBaselines

ns385:Method.description: Return a list of all of the coding scheme versions in which the supplied concept changed between the two supplied times (inclusive).
ns385:Method.name: getConceptChangeVersions

ns385:Method.description: Return the coding scheme version in which the supplied concept was created.
ns385:Method.name: getConceptCreationVersion

ns385:Method.description: Return the list of change events identifying the immediate descendants of the given concept reference.
ns385:Method.name: getDescendents

ns385:Method.description: Return the earliest baseline version in the list.
ns385:Method.name: getEarliestBaseline

ns385:Method.description: Return the list of available NCI-defined change events for the given concept and coding scheme version.
ns385:Method.name: getEditActionList

ns385:Method.description: Return the list of available NCI-defined change events for the given concept and date range.
ns385:Method.name: getEditActionList2

ns385:Method.description: Return the list of NCI-defined change events for the given concept and release; empty if not applicable.
ns385:Method.name: getEditActionList3

ns385:Method.description: Get the latest baseline in the list.
ns385:Method.name: getLatestBaseline

ns385:Method.description: Return detailed information about the particular system release.
ns385:Method.name: getSystemRelease

ns449:Method.description: List the coding schemes that are represented in the metadata index.
ns449:Method.name: listCodingSchemes

ns449:Method.description: Restrict the search to a particular coding scheme.
ns449:Method.name: restrictToCodingScheme

ns449:Method.description: Restrict the search to a particular property. Currently, this can be any element or attribute name from the OBO metadata schema. When we move to the 2006 version of the schema, there will be a method to get the available properties.
ns449:Method.name: restrictToProperties

ns449:Method.description: Restrict the search by the parents of the metadata elements. The OBO MetaData format is hierarchial - if you wish to restrict your search to properties that are under another property, provide the required property containers here.
ns449:Method.name: restrictToPropertyParents

ns449:Method.description: Restrict the result to the metadata elements that match the supplied string, using the supplied matching algorithm
ns449:Method.name: restrictToValue

ns449:Method.description: Apply all of the restrictions, and return the result.
ns449:Method.name: resolve

ns483:Method.description: Return the name assigned to this service extension. This name must be unique within context of the installed node and is used to register and lookup the extension through a LexBIGService.
ns483:Method.name: getName

ns483:Method.description: Return a description of the extension.
ns483:Method.name: getDescription

ns483:Method.description: Return an identifier for the extension provider.
ns483:Method.name: getProvider

ns483:Method.description: Return version information about the extension.
ns483:Method.name: getVersion

ns501:Method.description: Indicates whether or not the given reference satisfies criteria for this filter. Filters should _NOT_ be used for search criteria that can be done with built in restrictions. Filters are very inefficient.
ns501:Method.name: match

ns501:Method.description: Return the name assigned to this service extension. This name must be unique within context of the installed node and is used to register and lookup the extension through a LexBIGService.
ns501:Method.name: getName

ns501:Method.description: Return a description of the extension.
ns501:Method.name: getDescription

ns501:Method.description: Return an identifier for the extension provider.
ns501:Method.name: getProvider

ns501:Method.description: Return version information about the extension.
ns501:Method.name: getVersion
